One of your keyrings is locked. Unlock it to view the passwords it contains.

If keyring unlock is cancelled, a button is shown in the header bar.

Password properties reflect the type of password and which app it was stored by. If a password is tied to an account, the user can't remove it - since this risks making the account inoperable. Instead they'd have to use the app to remove the account.
Keyring switcher is only shown if there's more than one keyring. There's deliberatly no way to add keyrings.
These options are in Seahorse, but I have no idea what they are for.
To have this key signed, generate a signing code and present it to the person who is signing. Signing should always be done in person.
